### SETUP OPENVPN IN AWS FREE TIER ###

Using UBUNTU FREE TIER VM

Create an account

Spin up the vm

Make sure you create a key pair and choose
vms only that are free tier compatible

change the permissions of the downloaded keypair

"sudo chmod 400 yourkey.pem"

ssh into your vm from your local machine

"ssh -i key user@ip"

Once in the vm

Update the vm
"sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade"

Download an openvpn installation script from github

"wget https://git.io/vpn -O openvpn-install.sh"

Make the script executable

"sudo chmod +x openvpn-install.sh"

Run the sript

"sudo ./openvpn-install.sh"

The following prompts will pop up

Welcome to this OpenVPN road warrior installer!

Which protocol should OpenVPN use?
   1) UDP (recommended)
   2) TCP
Protocol [1]: 1

What port should OpenVPN listen to?
Port [1194]: 

Select a DNS server for the clients:
   1) Current system resolvers
   2) Google
   3) 1.1.1.1
   4) OpenDNS
   5) Quad9
   6) AdGuard
DNS server [1]: 2

Enter a name for the first client:
Name [client]: iphone

OpenVPN installation is ready to begin.
Press any key to continue...

Afterthis confirm the vpn is up and running

"sudo systemctl status openvpn-server@server.service"

The .ovpn file in my case was saved on the root folder 

-----
Go to your client machine

Copy the file from the server to your pc

scp -i serverkey user@ip:filelocation

Once the file is downloaded, download an openvpn client and connect using a file


